    "title": "Opinion Announcement - May 27, 2014",
    "transcript": {
        "title": null,
        "duration": 175.824,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 175.824,
                "byte_start": 107520,
                "byte_stop": 810736,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 6.667,
                        "byte_start": 107520,
                        "byte_stop": 134269,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 6.667,
                                "byte_start": 107520,
                                "byte_stop": 134269,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has our opinion in case 12-1117, Plumhoff v. Rickard."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 6.667,
                        "stop": 175.824,
                        "byte_start": 134269,
                        "byte_stop": 810736,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 6.667,
                                "stop": 20.702,
                                "byte_start": 134269,
                                "byte_stop": 190380,
                                "text": "This case concerns the question whether a group of police officers violated the Fourth Amendment\u0027s prohibition on unreasonable seizures when they shot a driver to put an end to a dangerous high-speed car chase."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.702,
                                "stop": 30.793,
                                "byte_start": 190380,
                                "byte_stop": 230713,
                                "text": "The relevant facts are as follows: The officers pulled over Donald Rickard in West Memphis, Arkansas when they noticed that he had a burned-out headlight."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.793,
                                "stop": 36.638,
                                "byte_start": 230713,
                                "byte_stop": 254119,
                                "text": "During the stop, Rickard acted suspiciously so an officer asked him to step out of the car."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 36.638,
                                "stop": 42.178,
                                "byte_start": 254119,
                                "byte_stop": 276271,
                                "text": "He instead drove off and fled east on an interstate and crossed then to Tennessee."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.178,
                                "stop": 50.059,
                                "byte_start": 276271,
                                "byte_stop": 307827,
                                "text": "Several police cruisers pursued him as he swerved in and out of traffic at times its speed exceeding 100 miles an hour."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.059,
                                "stop": 55.031,
                                "byte_start": 307827,
                                "byte_stop": 327680,
                                "text": "Rickard eventually turned off the interstate and continued fleeing on other roads."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.031,
                                "stop": 63.365,
                                "byte_start": 327680,
                                "byte_stop": 361012,
                                "text": "His car collided with a police car and spun out but he continued to try to escape and he collided with another police car."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 63.365,
                                "stop": 76.651,
                                "byte_start": 361012,
                                "byte_stop": 414198,
                                "text": "At that point, the officers drew their weapons, one of the officers pounded on the window of the car and when Rickard did not surrender and appeared to have his foot on the accelerator, the officer fired a total of fifteen shots."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.651,
                                "stop": 83.182,
                                "byte_start": 414198,
                                "byte_stop": 440320,
                                "text": "He nevertheless drove away, but he soon lost control of the car and crashed into a wall."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 83.182,
                                "stop": 86.402,
                                "byte_start": 440320,
                                "byte_stop": 453172,
                                "text": "Rickard and the passenger in his car died."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.402,
                                "stop": 91.037,
                                "byte_start": 453172,
                                "byte_stop": 471771,
                                "text": "Rickard\u0027s daughter sued the officers alleging that they had used excessive force."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.037,
                                "stop": 101.682,
                                "byte_start": 471771,
                                "byte_stop": 514299,
                                "text": "The District Court agreed and the Sixth Circuit affirmed holding that the officers had violated the Fourth Amendment and that they were not entitled to qualified immunity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.682,
                                "stop": 105.001,
                                "byte_start": 514299,
                                "byte_stop": 527569,
                                "text": "This is a tragic case but we reverse the decision below."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.001,
                                "stop": 118.151,
                                "byte_start": 527569,
                                "byte_stop": 580127,
                                "text": "First, we reject the argument that we lack jurisdiction under our decision in Johnson verus Jones, a case in which the only issue raised in an interlocutory appeal concerned the question of evidence sufficiency."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.151,
                                "stop": 120.679,
                                "byte_start": 580127,
                                "byte_stop": 590263,
                                "text": "Here, the officers raised legal issues."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.679,
                                "stop": 124.813,
                                "byte_start": 590263,
                                "byte_stop": 606877,
                                "text": "Second, we conclude that the officers did not violate the Fourth Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.813,
                                "stop": 130.543,
                                "byte_start": 606877,
                                "byte_stop": 629760,
                                "text": "Their use of deadly force to end this dangerous high-speed chase was objectively reasonable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.543,
                                "stop": 143.188,
                                "byte_start": 629760,
                                "byte_stop": 680333,
                                "text": "We further hold that the number of shots fired was not excessive under these circumstances and we conclude that the presence of a passenger in the car does not alter the inquiry as to Rickard himself."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.188,
                                "stop": 156.565,
                                "byte_start": 680333,
                                "byte_stop": 733832,
                                "text": "We hold finally that even if the officers had violated the Fourth Amendment, no clearly established law prescribed their conduct at that time, and therefore, they were entitled to qualified immunity on that ground."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 156.565,
                                "stop": 164.741,
                                "byte_start": 733832,
                                "byte_stop": 766537,
                                "text": "For these and other reasons said out in our opinion, we reverse the decision on the Sixth Circuit and remand for further proceedings consistent with this opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 164.741,
                                "stop": 175.824,
                                "byte_start": 766537,
                                "byte_stop": 810736,
                                "text": "Our decision is unanimous except that Justice Ginsburg does not join parts 3(a) and 3(b), and Justice Breyer does not join part 3(b)."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
